<EFX_BUSINESS>
<A NAME="FIS_BUSINESS"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT 55.45PT;TEXT-INDENT: -55.45PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A NAME="ATRC-20151231X10K_HTM__TOC315767339">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	IT
</FONT>
<A NAME="ATRC-20151231X10K_HTM_BUSINESS">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	EM&nbsp;1.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	BUSINES
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	S
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We are a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	leading atrial fibrillation (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Afib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	solutions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	partner providing innovative products, professional education and support for clinical science to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reduce the economic and social burden of atrial fibrillation.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	several
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	product lines for the ablation of cardiac tissue
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, including our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Isolator
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Synergy Ablation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	System
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the first and only surgical device approved
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	by the United States Food and Drug Administration (FDA)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for the treatment of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	persistent and longstanding persistent forms of Afib in patients undergoing certain open concomitant procedures.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We also offer a variety of minimally invasive ablation devices and access tools to facilitate the growing trend in less invasive cardiac and thoracic surgery. Our cryoICE
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	cryosurgery
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	product line
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	offers a variety of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	cryoablation devices.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	AtriClip
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Left
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Atrial Appendage
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Exclusion System
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is the most wi
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	dely sold device worldwide specifically designed to occlude
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	heart&#x2019;s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	left atrial appendage
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	(LAA)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	believe cardiothoracic surgeons are adopting
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ablation and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	LAA management (LAAM)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	devices
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for the treatment of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Afib and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reduction of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Afib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	-
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	relate
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	d complications such as stroke.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Cardiothoracic surgeons have adopted our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	radiofrequency (RF) ablation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and cryoablation systems to treat A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	in an
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	estimated
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	195,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	patients since
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	2004
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, and we believe that we are currently the market leader in the surgical treatment of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our products are utilized by cardiothoracic surgeons during
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	both
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	open-heart
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	minimally invasive
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	surgical
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	procedures
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, either on a concomitant or sole-therapy basis
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. During a concomitant procedure, the surgeon ablates cardiac tissue and/or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	exclude
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s the left atrial appendage, secondary, or concomitant, to a primary cardiac procedure such as a
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	valve
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	repair or
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	replacement
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	or coronary
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	artery
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	bypass
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	graft
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	(CABG)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Isolator
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Synergy System, which includes our Isolator Synergy clamps,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	RF
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	generator and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	related
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	switchbox
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	approved
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	FDA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for the treatment of persistent and long-standing persistent Afib concomitant to other open-heart surgical procedures such as coronary artery bypass grafting and/or valve replacement or repair.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	To date, none of our other products have been approved by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	FDA
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	specifically
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	for the treatment of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our 510(k)-cleared RF and cryo ablation products are indicated for the ablation of cardiac tissue and/or treatment of cardiac arrhythmias.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In addition, our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	cryoICE probe
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is cleared for blocking pain by temporarily ablating peripheral nerves.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our AtriClip products are 510(k)-cleared with an indication for occlusion of the LAA, under direct visualization, concomitant to other open cardiac surgical procedures.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We recently acquired nContact
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Surgical, Inc. (nContact&#x2122;),
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	a leader in minimally invasive technology for epicardial ablation.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We also have a line of reusable surgical instruments typically used for cardiac valve replacement or repair.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We anticipate that substantially all of our revenue for the foreseeable future will relate to products we currently sell, or are in the process of developing, which surgeons use to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ablate cardiac tissue,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to exclude
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the left atrial appendage
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to perform mitral and aortic valve replacement and repair and/or to ablate peripheral nerves during cardiothoracic surgery.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	affects approximately 1% of the population in the United States. It is the most common cardiac arrhythmia, or irregular heartbeat, encountered in clinical practice and accounts for more doctor visits and hospital days than any other cardiac arrhythmia.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	When a patient is in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	abnormal electrical impulses cause the atria, or upper chambers of the heart, to fibrillate, or quiver, at rapid rates of 400 to 600 beats per minute. As a result, blood in the atria may become static, increas
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ing the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	risk that a blood clot will form and cause a stroke or other serious complications. Symptoms of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	may include heart palpitations, dizziness, fatigue and shortness of breath, and these symptoms may be debilitating and life threatening in some cases.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Patients often progress from being in Afib intermittently to being in Afib continuously.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	often occurs in conjunction
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	cardiovascular disease
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	including
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	hypertension, congestive heart failure, left ventricular dysfunction, coronary artery disease and valvular disease.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In the United States
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of America
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	we sell our products to medical centers through our direct sales force. AtriCure Europe
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	B.V., our wholly-owned subsidiary incorporated and based in the Netherlands, markets and sells our products throughout Europe
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the Middle East
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	I
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	n certain markets, such as Germany
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, France, the United Kingdom
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and the Benelux region,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	sales are made
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	directly to medical centers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, with the remaining sales being made through distributors
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In other international markets
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	we sell our products to
</FONT>
</P>

</FONT>
</P>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#ATRC-20151231X10K_HTM_TABLEOFCONTENTS">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	distributors
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	who in turn sell them to end users
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. Our business is primarily transacted in U.S.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	D
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ollars with the exception of transactions with our European subsidiary which are transacted in Euros
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	or British Pounds
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	AtriCure, Inc. was
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	incorporated in the State of Delaware on October&nbsp;31, 2000 in connection with a spin-off transaction from Enable Medical Corporation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	(Enable)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	in which shares of our common stock were distributed to Enable shareholders. The spin-off was intended to allow us to focus on the development of products designed to treat A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and to raise capital for that purpose, while Enable continued its broader research and manufacturing activities. On August&nbsp;5, 2005, we completed an initial public offering of our common stock. On August&nbsp;10, 2005, we acquired Enable Medical Corporation, the manufacturer of our Isolator clamps, which are an essential part of our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Isolator
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Synergy System.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	On December 31, 2013, we acquired Endoscopic Technologies, Inc. (Estech
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-SIZE:5PT;TOP:-4PT;POSITION:RELATIVE;LINE-HEIGHT:100%">
	&#xAE;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	), a medical device company focused primarily on RF ablation products used in cardiothoracic surgery. On October 13, 2015, we acquired nContact
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	a medical device company focused primarily on minimally invasive epicardial ablation products. We have two operating subsidiaries: (i) AtriCure Europe, B.V., a company incorporated under the laws of the Netherlands in December 2005 and (ii) AtriCure, LLC, a limited liability company organized under the laws of Delaware in October 2012.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Market Overview
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is the most commonly diagnosed sustained cardiac arrhythmia, and affects more than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	30
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million people worldwide, including more than
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	five
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;million
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#FF0000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	in the United States
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. According to data from the Framingham Heart Study, a study originally undertaken by the National Heart Institute (now known as the National Heart, Lung and Blood Institute), it is estimated that the incidence of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	doubles with each decade of an adult&#x2019;s life. At age 40, remaining lifetime risk for A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is 26% for men and 23% for women. A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is an under-diagnosed condition due in large part to the fact that patients with A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	often have mild or no symptoms and their A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is only diagnosed when they seek treatment for an associated condition, such as a stroke or heart disease. We believe that increasing awareness of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and improved diagnostic screening will result in an increased number of patients diagnosed with A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. Also, since the prevalence of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	increases with age, there will likely be an increase in the number of diagnosed A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	patients in the United States as the population ages.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We believe that the same trends in the United States apply globally, as in many geographies incidence of Afib is increasing as the population ages.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is a condition that doctors often find difficult to treat and, historically, there has been no widely accepted long-term cure for A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	This difficulty is exacerbated with more serious forms of Afib, which are typically classified as &#x201C;persistent&#x201D; and &#x201C;long-standing persistent&#x201D; Afib.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Doctors typically begin treating A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	with drugs, which are often ineffective, not well-tolerated and may be associated with serious side effects
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, including the risk of bleeding
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. Patients who cannot effectively be treated with drugs may be candidates to undergo catheter-based procedures to treat their A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. To perform a catheter ablation, an electrophysiologist
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	inserts a flexible catheter into the inside of the heart, typically through the femoral vein
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. Catheter-based procedures
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, especially for more serious forms of Afib, are generally not indicated for patients with persistent or long-standing persistent Afib because they
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ar
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	e often technically challenging and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	can be associated with serious complications
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. Multiple clinical studies
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	shown that catheter ablation for the more serious forms of Afib produces
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	inconsistent results. Implantable devices, such as pacemakers and defibrillators, are sometimes used to reduce the frequency and symptoms of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	although they are not designed to treat the underlying disease. In the past, an open-heart surgical procedure known as the &#x201C;cut and sew Maze&#x201D; was used to treat A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, but this procedure has not been widely adopted because it is technically challenging, highly invasive and involves long recovery times.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Of the patients undergoing open-heart surgery
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	globally
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, we estimate that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	over 250,000
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#FF0000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	are potential candidates for surgical ablation using our products.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Today, we estimate that approximately 25-30% of those candidates are being treated in one form or another, but many of these are not treated properly or fully.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Of the population diagnosed with A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	a large percentage
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of these patients are symptomatic and do not respond to drug therapy or are intolerant to the drugs used to treat A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Additionally,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	there is a large population of patients
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	who have no other underlying cardiac disease but who suffer from serious forms of Afib. Many of these patients fail traditional therapies, and thus we believe could benefit
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	a &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	minimally invasive
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	or hybrid
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	treatment using our products.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In addition, Afib is thought to be responsible for approximately 15% to 20% of the estimated 700,000 strokes that occur annually in the United States. According to the American Heart Association, the risk of stroke is five times higher in people with Afib. Approximately 35% of Afib patients will have a stroke in their lifetime, and Afib-related strokes tend to be severe. Studies suggest that 25% of people who have an Afib-related stroke die within the first thirty days following their stroke and more than 40% are permanently bedridden. Afib accounts for $6,700,000 in hospitalization-related costs in the United States each year and an estimated $5,000 in office visits annually. Indirect costs, such as the management of Afib-related strokes, are believed to be significant. Because of the risk of stroke, and the significant cost burden on the healthcare system, more and more surgeons are routinely addressing the LAA in procedures performed to treat Afib. In addition, current practice guidelines state that the LAA should be excluded or removed, when possible, during cardiac surgery in patients at risk of developing postoperative Afib. We believe that our AtriClip system is safer, more effective and easier to use than other products and techniques for excluding the LAA, and, because of this, we believe that the market for the AtriClip system is large and represents a significant growth opportunity.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	The AtriCure Solution and Products
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Competing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	surgical and catheter-based ablation devices are not ideal for safely, rapidly and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	reliably creating
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	lesions
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	that completely and permanently
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	block the abnormal electrical impulses that cause A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, particularly for patients with more chronic forms of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	or patients who have failed single or multiple catheter ablations.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	O
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ur products, including our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Isolator
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Synergy System, enable cardiac surgeons to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	mimic the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	cut and sew Maze
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	procedure
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	but
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	with a faster, less invasive and less technically challenging approach
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our clinical studies for the use of our products to treat A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	are ongoing. Leading cardiothoracic surgeons and electrophysiologists, including those who serve or who have served as consultants to us, have published results of initial clinical studies utilizing our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Isolator
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Synergy System. The results of these studies are promising in terms of efficacy, ease of use and safety.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	two
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	primary product lines for cardiac tissue ablation and a product line for left atrial appendage exclusion:
</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Product lines for cardiac tissue ablation:
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Electrosurgical Unit (ESU)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	E
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	SU is a compact power generator
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for use with COBRA Fusion ablation products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. We generally

</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 21.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;FONT-STYLE:NORMAL;FONT-SIZE:10PT;;">
	2.)
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:3PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:3PT;WIDTH:3PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	cryoICE
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Cryoablation System.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The cryoICE
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	cryoablation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	system
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	consists of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	cryoICE BOX
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	generator along with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	a range of
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	cryoI
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	CE single use and reusable cryosurgery probes. The cryoICE
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	cryoablation s
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ystem is used to ablate cardiac tissue for the treatment of cardiac arrhythmias and to provide temporary pain relief to thoracic surgery patients
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	via
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ablation of peripheral nerves
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The probes come in a variety of configurations, with the primary difference being flexibility of the distal end of the probe. This flexibility provides for a variety of use cases covering both open and minimally invasive surgery.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:22.3PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Product line for left atrial appendage
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	management
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT 48.95PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;TEXT-DECORATION:UNDERLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	AtriClip System.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	AtriClip system is designed to exclude the left atrial appendage by
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	mechanically clamping the appendage from
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the outside, eliminating blood flow between the left atrial appendage and the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	atrium while
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	avoiding contact with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	circulating blood
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. We believe that
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	AtriClip system is potentially safer, more effective and easier to use
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	than other
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	available
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	products and techniques
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	permanently excluding the left atrial appendage
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The AtriClip portfolio includes
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	a range of devices with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	different
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	size clips, as well as different applier
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	lengths and deployment features.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	These different configurations allow for a variety of uses covering both open and minimally invasive surgery.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	In addition to the above product lines we also sell enabling technologies including our Lumitip&#x2122; dissector
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	s and the Estech line of reusable cardiac surgery instruments
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. The Lumitip dissector is used by surgeons to separate tissues to provide access to key anatomical structures that are targeted for ablation.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The Estech cardiac surgery instruments are used during surgical procedures for repair or replacement of certain heart valves.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Current A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;COLOR:#000000;">
	Treatment Alternatives
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Physicians
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	usually begin treating A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	patients with a variety of drugs intended to prevent blood clots, control heart rate or restore the heart to normal sinus rhythm. If a patient&#x2019;s A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	cannot be adequately controlled with drug therapy, doctors may perform one of several procedures that vary depending on the severity of the A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	symptoms and whether or not the patient suffers from other forms of heart disease.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A 2014 report of the American College of Cardiology/American Heart Association Task Force on Practice Guidelines and the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Heart Rhythm Society
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	set forth
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	guidelines for the management of patients with Afib.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	guidelines state
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	: &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:24PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:24PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 20.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:4PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:4PT;WIDTH:4PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	An Afib surgical ablation procedure is reasonable for selected patients with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	undergoing cardiac surgery
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for other indications
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	; &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:24PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:24PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 20.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:4PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:4PT;WIDTH:4PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	A &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	stand-alone A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	surgical ablation procedure may be reasonable for selected patients with highly symptomatic Afib not well managed with other approaches.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	T
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	reatment alternatives include:
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:24PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:24PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 20.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:4PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:4PT;WIDTH:4PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Drugs.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Pharmaceutical options called anti-arrhythmics are available to treat Afib. Depending on a patient&#x2019;s severity of the disease and heart condition, physicians typically administer these medications in a hospital setting with continuous monitoring. If the patient goes back into a normal rhythm, the physician will often prescribe a similar anti-arrhythmic to try to prevent a recurrence of Afib. The effectiveness of drug therapy varies based on the patient population and the drug being prescribed, among other factors. Often times, pharmaceuticals to thin the blood (anti-coagulants) are prescribed due to the increased risk of stroke for patients who also have Afib.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:24PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:24PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 20.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:4PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:4PT;WIDTH:4PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Implantable Devices.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Implantable
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	devices, such as defibrillators and pacemakers, can be effective in reducing the symptoms and frequency of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	episodes, but neither device is intended to treat A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. Patients may continue to experience the adverse effects of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	as well as some of the symptoms and complications, including dizziness, fatigue, palpitations and stroke, because the A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	continues.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<TABLE STYLE="WIDTH:100%;" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0">
<TR>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:24PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:24PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="WIDTH: 20.00PT; DISPLAY: INLINE;">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:SYMBOL;FONT-SIZE:8PT;;">
	&#xB7;
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
<TD STYLE="WIDTH:4PT;">
<P STYLE="WIDTH:4PT;WIDTH:4PT;FONT-SIZE:0PT;">
</P>
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">
<P STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT;MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Catheter
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	Ablation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Catheter ablation is an ablation procedure that is typically performed by an electrophysiologist. The ablations are made from the inside of the heart using a flexible catheter. The heart is reached via a blood vessel, most commonly through the femoral vein. In proportion to the prevalence of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, only a small number of catheter-based A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	treatments are performed each year in the United States.
</FONT>
</P>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	With the exception of the Isolator Synergy System, which may be promoted according to its FDA-approved indication for patients with persistent and long-standing persistent Afib undergoing certain open-heart procedures, we do not promote our products specifically for Afib. Nevertheless, physicians
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	have adopted our products for use in open-heart and minimally invasive procedures for the treatment of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. During elective open-heart surgical procedures, such as bypass or valve surgery, cardiothoracic surgeons use our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	ablation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	systems to treat patients with a pre-existing history of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. Surgeons report that ablation using our products generally adds approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	20 to 3
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	0 minutes to an open-heart surgical procedure. Surgeons use our products to perform cardiac procedures that may vary depending on the length of time a patient has been diagnosed with A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	and whether the patient&#x2019;s A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	is intermittent, known as paroxysmal, or more continuous
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	(non-paroxysmal)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	which is typically further classified
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	as persistent, long-standing persistent or permanent
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	Patients who have been diagnosed with A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for a longer duration and have non-paroxysmal forms of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	generally receive more extensive ablation procedures than patients who have been diagnosed with A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	for a shorter duration or who have paroxysmal A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	. Additionally, during an open-heart procedure, physicians
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	may
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	use our AtriClip system to exclude the left atrial appendage
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	, which has been reported to add less than one minute to a procedure.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;COLOR:#000000;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE="1">
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	4
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>

</HR>
<P STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:ALWAYS">
	&nbsp;
</P>
<A NAME="eolPage7"></A>
<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<A HREF="#ATRC-20151231X10K_HTM_TABLEOFCONTENTS">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Table of Contents
</FONT>
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	For those patients with A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	who do not require a concomitant open-heart surgical procedure, surgeons have used our Isolator
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	clamps
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and related products for minimally invasive A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	treatment procedures. These procedures have generally been performed through minimally invasive incisions without the need to place patients on a heart-lung bypass machine. Surgeons have reported that the procedure takes approximately two to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	four
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	hours and that the average hospitalization period has typically been two to five days. Similar to the open-heart surgical procedure, patients who have non-paroxysmal forms of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	generally require an expanded lesion set that mimics the cut and sew Maze procedure. Our multifunctional pens are often used during these procedures to enable physicians to perform additional ablations.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Physicians are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	performing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	an emerging minimally invasive stand-alone
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	staged
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	procedure which combines epicardial
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	(surgical)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ablation (ablation on the outside of the heart) with endocardial ablation and mapping techniques (from the inside of the heart).
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	This procedure involves
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	hav
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the epicardial procedure performed on the first day of hospitalization and the catheter ablation and mapping performed at a later time.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Physicians are reporting that they are performing this procedure, also known as a hybrid procedure, utilizing
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	certain of our products
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to primarily treat patients who have non-paroxysmal forms of A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Leverage Product Portfolio, Labeling and Cross-Selling Opportunities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We believe we have the most comprehensive offering of cardiac ablation and left atrial appendage exclusion products in the market. We plan to leverage our leading product portfolio to facilitate cross-selling of our products as well as to drive market share gains through competitive account conversions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Expand Adoption of Our Minimally Invasive Products.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We believe that the catalysts for expanded adoption of our minimally invasive products include procedural advancements, such as the hybrid procedure, and the publication of peer-reviewed articles, which we believe will help validate the successful, long-term use of our products for patients with A
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	fib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. We believe that ongoing research activities, including clinical trials, new procedural techniques and anticipated presentations and publications will create an increased demand for our minimally invasive products.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
</P>
<P>

</FONT>

<DIV STYLE="WIDTH:100%">

<A HREF="#ATRC-20151231X10K_HTM_TABLEOFCONTENTS">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">

</FONT>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
	&nbsp;
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	Evaluate Acquisition Opportunities
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	In the past two years, we have acquired two companies that we believe further expand our ability to establish a platform for long-term revenue growth. We expect to continue to be opportunistic with respect to acquisitions where it makes strategic and financial sense.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Clinical Trials
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	December 2011 FDA approval
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	of our Isolator Synergy System
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	include
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	d
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-STYLE:ITALIC;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	requirement to
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	implement a 350-patient post-approval study
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	(PAS)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	The PAS was designed to evaluate the long-term safety and efficacy of our Isolator Synergy System in the treatment of persistent and long-standing persistent Afib in patients undergoing open-heart procedures. Enrollment in the trial was completed in October 2014 with 365 patients at 40 medical centers. We expect to release preliminary data from the study in early 2016, with a complete report expected to be published in 2017.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We conducted the Dual Epicardial Endocardial Persistent Atrial Fibrillation (Staged DEEP AF) Feasibility clinical trial to evaluate use of the Isolator Synergy System for the treatment of Afib in a two-part procedure where a minimally invasive surgical ablation
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	procedure
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	is performed first, and an intracardiac catheter mapping and ablation procedure is then performed on a different day during the same hospitalization. Enrollment in the Staged DEEP AF
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Feasibility
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	trial was completed during the fourth quarter of 2013, with 30 patients enrolled at six medical centers.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We submitted an Investigational Device Exemption (IDE) application for the Staged DEEP
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	AF
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	pivotal trial to FDA in May 2014. The Staged DEEP
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	AF
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	pivotal trial evaluates the safety and efficacy of the Isolator Synergy System when used in a staged approach, where a minimally invasive surgical ablation procedure is first performed, and the patient undergoes the intracardiac catheter procedure approximately 90-120 days later.&nbsp;FDA approval to enroll up to 220 subjects at 23 domestic medical centers and two international medical centers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	was received during the third quarter of 2014. Enrollment began during the first quarter of 2015, and there are currently
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	30
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	patients enrolled and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	twelve
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	sites initiated.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We also conducted a Stroke Feasibility clinical trial with the AtriClip System.&nbsp;The trial evaluates the initial procedural safety and efficacy of the AtriClip System for stroke prophylaxis (prevention of stroke) in patients with non-valvular Afib in whom long term oral anticoagulation therapy is medically contraindicated.&nbsp;We had approval to enroll up to 30 patients at seven medical centers during the course of the trial.&nbsp;Enrollment began in the first quarter of 2014 and involved twelve patients.&nbsp;A Pre-Submission Meeting was held with FDA during the first quarter of 2015 to discuss the early termination of enrollment in the Stroke Feasibility clinical trial and proceeding to the pivotal trial. FDA has approved the termination of the feasibility study at twelve enrolled subjects.&nbsp;The pivotal trial design is under discussion with FDA.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We are in the beginning stages of our ATLAS study, which is a non-IDE randomized pilot study evaluating outcomes of patients with risk factors for developing postoperative Afib as well as risk of bleeding on oral anticoagulation.&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	There are two types of patients subject to this study:
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	those receiving&nbsp;prophylactic exclusion of the left atrial appendage with the AtriClip
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	device
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	concomitant to cardiac surgery and those with a postoperative
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Afib
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	diagnosis who are medically managed.&nbsp;At full capacity, we expect to enroll approximately 2,000 patients at up to twenty sites.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	began enrollment in February 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, and there is
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	currently one patient enrolled and two sites initiated.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We are in the beginning stages of our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	c
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	ryoanalgesia
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	study (
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	FROST
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	)
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	, which is a non-IDE randomized pilot study evaluating whether intraoperative intercostal cryoanalgesia in conjunction with standard of care provides improved analgesic efficacy in patients undergoing unilateral thoracotomy cardiac procedures as compared to current standard of care. The
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	study will involve
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	treatment arm subjects
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	who
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	will receive intercostal cryoanalgesia in conjunction with standard post-operative pain management and control arm subjects
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	who
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	will receive standard post-operative pain management only. At full capacity, we expect to enroll 100 patients at up to five sites.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	initiated one site
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	and expect to begin enrollment in
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	the first quarter of 2016
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	.&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	We are also pursuing a non-IDE trial in Europe, CEASE AF, to compare staged hybrid ablation treatment (minimally invasive surgical ablation procedure is first performed and the patient undergoes the intracardiac catheter procedure approximately 91-180 days later) versus catheter ablation alone. We expect the study to have an enrollment of approximately 210 patients across ten sites.
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	There are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	currently three
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	patients enrolled and six sites initiated.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	With the acquisition of nContact, we are conducting the CONVERGE
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	IDE
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	clinical trial. The CONVERGE pivotal trial evaluates the safety and efficacy of the nContact
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	EPi-Sense Guided
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Coagulation System with
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	VisiTrax technology
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	to treat symptomatic persistent Afib patients who are refractory or intolerant to at least one Class I and/or III anti-arrhythmic drug. We have
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	FDA approval to enroll up to 153 subjects at fifteen domestic medical centers and two international medical centers
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	. &nbsp;
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Enrollment began during the first quarter of 2014, and there are
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	currently 39 patients
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	enrolled and
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	thirteen
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	domestic sites initiated.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:13.5PT 0PT 0PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;FONT-WEIGHT:BOLD;">
	Sales, Marketing and Medical Education
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:4.5PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	Our
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	employees supporting
</FONT>

	approximately
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	sales
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	territories. We select our sales personnel based on their expertise, sales experience and reputation in the medical device industry
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
	,
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

<P STYLE="MARGIN:9PT 0PT 0PT;TEXT-INDENT:24.5PT;FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;FONT-SIZE: 10PT">
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>

</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>

<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="DISPLAY: INLINE;">
